| 1 |  | #P_ax-c11 | |- ( A. x x = y -> ( A. x x = y -> A. y x = y ) ) |
| 2 | 1 | #P_pm2.43i | |- ( A. x x = y -> A. y x = y ) |
| 3 |  | #P_equcomi | |- ( x = y -> y = x ) |

\
 Rederivation of ~ ax-c11n from original version ~ ax-c11 .  See theorem ~ axc11 for the derivation of ~ ax-c11 from ~ ax-c11n . This theorem should not be referenced in any proof.  Instead, use ~ ax-c11n above so that uses of ~ ax-c11n can be more easily identified, or use ~ aecom-o when this form is needed for studies involving ~ ax-c11 and omitting ~ ax-5 .
